<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="17" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d17">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/4525½</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-07">
                                    <hi rend="italic">7 May, 1917</hi>
                                </date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: The practicability and
                            wisdom of carrying out this very useful suggestion depends, as in so
                            many other cases, upon finding the right man,—a really capable man who
                            will be equally able and well poised and sensible, not likely to swell
                            with importance and instruct us every day by cable. Have you such a man
                            in mind, or do you think you could find one?</p>
                        <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. W.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>